  <description><![CDATA[<p>The Ylläs Saaga Hotel is a modern hotel located beside the Lappish fells - it's right in the centre of the Ylläsjärvi side of the fell, next to the ski lifts, ski school and ski hire shop. The cosy rooms are furnished to a high standard, and have everything you need for a week in Lapland, plus many of our rooms have views over the fell. Customers who would like a little more space may also like the <a data-udi="umb://document/d6a5b04bc7044b2faaf1e005d8d9bc7c" href="/{localLink:umb://document/d6a5b04bc7044b2faaf1e005d8d9bc7c}" title="Yllas Saaga Apartments">Ylläs Saaga Apartments</a> which are self-catering, but have the option to pre-book half board (at a supplement) which is taken in the hotel. </p>
<h2>Slope side location</h2>
<p>Located on the Ylläsjärvi side of the fell, the Ylläs Saaga Hotel offers convenientaccess onto the slopes. The Saaga Hotel, village and slopes of Ylläsjärvi are on the southern side of the fells, and the village and slopes of Äkäslompolo are located on the northern side of <a data-udi="umb://document/cc68d9ee210a4063af0a51552472263c" href="/{localLink:umb://document/cc68d9ee210a4063af0a51552472263c}" title="Yllas">Ylläs</a>. Once you have made it to the top station of the lifts, you can choose which direction you want to take. The slopes are varied, and often relatively uncrowded - ideal for skiers and boarders who are just starting out.</p>
<h2>Soothing Spa </h2>
<p>After a day of exploring Ylläs, there is nowhere better to relax and unwind than in the hotels own wellness centre. Have a dip in the indoor pool, soothe any aches and pains in the hot tub, or warm up in the sauna and steam room. For the younger guests, there is also a children's pool and splash area. Pamper yourself and book a massage or treatment with the hotel reception (payable locally). Alternatively, if you are keen to keep up your fitness levels there is also an on-site gym (reservation only). </p>
<h2>Warm up and relax</h2>
<p>The Fireplace Bar is the perfect place to come after a day on the slopes to unwind and warm up with a couple of drinks. Later in the evening you can enjoy a three course evening meal taken at the Biegga buffet restaurant, which has fantastic views across the fells and Ylläsjärvi. For a little extra, you can enjoy a meal at the à la carte restaurant - Tsohka, the restaurant's menu is inspired by Lappish ingredients and local flavours. Guests receive a discount for the à la carte restaurant, please inform the reception team 6pm the day before if you want to have dinner in Tsohka.</p>]]></description>
